        <div n="952BROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">ONIONS</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-1"> Come, follow me by the smell, 3}&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-2"> Here's delicate onions to sell,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-3"> I promise to use you well.</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-4"> They make the blood warmer,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-5"> You'll feed like a farmer:</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-6"> For this is every cook's opinion,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-7"> No savoury dish without an onion;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-8"> But lest your kissing should be spoiled,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-9"> Your onions must be thoroughly boiled;Or else you may spareYour mistress a share,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-10"> The secret will never be known;She cannot discoverThe breath of her lover</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-952BROGP-line-11"> But think it as sweet as her own.952BROGP   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
